  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6820 sitting directly between massive gamma walls at 6820 (+75.4B) and 6830 (+75.5B), dealers are actively selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime confirms dealers will continue selling rallies and buying dips, creating strong mean-reversion dynamics around these levels. Given the wall_break event and proximity to max positive gamma at 6830, expect heavy dealer selling pressure if price pushes higher, while the 6800 level (+36.3B) provides downside support.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should face strong resistance and likely reverse lower from the 6820-6830 zone.",
